C. Germany (Bavaria)
Date: Tue 11 Feb 2020
Source: Reuters [edited]
https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-health-germany-cases/germany-confirms-two-more-cases-of-coronavirus-raising-overall-number-to-16-idUSKBN2052GT


Germany on Tuesday [11 Feb 2020] confirmed 2 more cases of coronavirus in the southern state of Bavaria, raising the overall number of known cases in Europe's most populous country to 16.

The 2 new cases of coronavirus are related to infections among staff at a company in the Starnberg district west of Munich, the Bavarian health ministry said. Car supplier Webasto said last month [January 2020] a Chinese employee had tested positive for the virus upon returning to China following a visit to the headquarters near Munich. The employee apparently infected several German colleagues during the visit.

[Byline: Michael Nienaber]

